## 📚 Complete Examples

### **Example 1: Full Training Pipeline**

```bash
# 1. Get method recommendation
lmtool recommend method --model-size 0.124 --vram 8

# 2. Generate configuration
lmtool config generate --output config.json --method lora

# 3. Validate configuration
lmtool config validate config.json

# 4. Train model
lmtool train run \
    --model gpt2 \
    --dataset ./data/train.jsonl \
    --method lora \
    --epochs 3 \
    --output ./outputs/model

# 5. Evaluate model
lmtool evaluate run \
    --model ./outputs/model \
    --dataset ./data/test.jsonl \
    --report ./reports/eval.md

# 6. Benchmark against base
lmtool evaluate benchmark \
    --base gpt2 \
    --finetuned ./outputs/model \
    --dataset ./data/test.jsonl \
    --report ./reports/benchmark.md
```

### **Example 2: QLoRA Training for Large Model**

```bash
# Check hardware requirements
lmtool recommend hardware 7 --method qlora

# Get configuration recommendations
lmtool recommend config qlora --dataset-size 10000

# Train with QLoRA
lmtool train run \
    --model meta-llama/Llama-2-7b-hf \
    --dataset ./data/large_dataset.jsonl \
    --source local \
    --max-samples 10000 \
    --method qlora \
    --4bit \
    --grad-checkpoint \
    --epochs 2 \
    --batch-size 2 \
    --lora-r 16 \
    --lora-alpha 64 \
    --output ./outputs/llama_qlora
```

### **Example 3: Batch Evaluation**

```bash
# Evaluate multiple checkpoints
for checkpoint in ./outputs/checkpoints/*; do
    lmtool evaluate run \
        --model $checkpoint \
        --dataset ./data/test.jsonl \
        --report ./reports/eval_$(basename $checkpoint).md
done
```

